<div class="card mb-g">

	<h4 class="card-header">
	    jQuery <span class="fw-300">throttle / debounce</span> 
	    <small>
	        Sometimes, less is more!
	    </small>
	</h4>

	<div class="card-body">

		<p>
			jQuery throttle / debounce allows you to rate-limit your functions in multiple useful ways. Passing a delay and callback to <code>$.throttle</code> returns a new function that will execute no more than once every delay milliseconds. Passing a delay and callback to <code>$.debounce</code> returns a new function that will execute only once, coalescing multiple sequential calls into a single execution at either the very beginning or end.
		</p>

		<h4 class="mt-4">
			Throttling
		</h4>
		<p>
			You can pass a delay and function to <code>$.throttle</code> to get a new function, that when called repetitively, executes the original function (in the same context and with all arguments passed through) no more than once every delay milliseconds.
		</p>

		<div class="row mb-g">
			<div class="col-sm-6">
				<h5 class="frame-heading p-0 bg-white mb-2 mt-0">Throttled with <code>no_trailing</code> specified as false or unspecified:</h5>
				<img src="img/demo/throttle.png" alt="throttle" class="mt-2 img-fluid">
			</div>
			<div class="col-sm-6">
				<h5 class="frame-heading p-0 bg-white mb-2 mt-0">Throttled with <code>no_trailing</code> specified as true: </h5>
				<img src="img/demo/throttle-no_trailing.png" alt="throttle-no_trailing" class="mt-2 img-fluid">
			</div>
		</div>

		<h4 class="mt-4">
			Debouncing
		</h4>
		<p>
			You can pass a delay and function to <code>$.debounce</code> to get a new function, that when called repetitively, executes the original function just once per “bunch” of calls, effectively coalescing multiple sequential calls into a single execution at either the beginning or end.
		</p>

		<div class="row mb-g">
			<div class="col-sm-6">
				<h5 class="frame-heading p-0 bg-white mb-2 mt-0">Debounced with <code>at_begin</code> specified as false or unspecified: :</h5>
				<img src="img/demo/debounce.png" alt="throttle" class="mt-2 img-fluid">
			</div>
			<div class="col-sm-6">
				<h5 class="frame-heading p-0 bg-white mb-2 mt-0">Debounced with <code>at_begin</code> specified as true:  </h5>
				<img src="img/demo/debounce-at_begin.png" alt="throttle-no_trailing" class="mt-2 img-fluid">
			</div>
		</div>			
		
	</div>
									
</div>
